Install ubuntu or ubuntu server
Open command line

Update apt-get:
sudo apt-get update

Install git:
sudo apt-get install git

create a folder for the project
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/wmuCS4900Project/PalermoPOS.git
git pull
git checkout release

Install curl:
sudo apt-get install curl 

get key for rvm
gpg --keyserver hkp://keys.gnupg.net --recv-keys 409B6B1796C275462A1703113804BB82D39DC0E3
gpg2 --keyserver hkp://keys.gnupg.net --recv-keys 409B6B1796C275462A1703113804BB82D39DC0E3

Install RVM:
\curl -L https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable --ruby

run 
/home/username/.rvm/scripts/rvm
Reopen command line

Install node.js:
sudo apt-get install nodejs

Update gems:
sudo gem update --system

Install bundler:
sudo gem install bundler

Install webkit prereqs
sudo apt-get install libqt4-dev libqtwebkit-dev

Install rails:
sudo gem install rails --version=5.0.0.1

Install other required gems (in the install folder)
bundle install

Install mysql:
sudo apt-get install mysql-server

Run mysql
mysql -u root -p

Run rails (in another window from the install folder) in development mode:
rails s
